I’ve been working on a project that I'm excited to share! I just finished designing a yard sign for @getridwell, a new zero-waste service in the Bay Area who offer bi-weekly household pickups of common hard-to-recycle items that are usually destined for the landfill. They pick up things like thin plastics, lightbulbs, textiles and styrofoam - and find non-traditional recycle, upcycle, and reuse opportunities for them. They also support local nonprofits AND share their transparency data.  I love what they are doing and you might love it too! Try @getridwell for FREE using the link - get.ridwell.com/sophie-tivona - and request a yard sign proudly designed by me!

Last painting of the year/last leaf on the tree. 🍂

This year, I didn’t meet my step goal or lose weight. I didn’t achieve my professional or financial goals. But 2022 was rich in so many ways… I drove across the country -and back - with my partner; I created a community on Patreon that has enriched my life in a way I could never have imagined; I taught over 60!!! classes and felt my skills as a teacher expand and grow; I spent my savings painting, designing, and printing dozens of new products; I supported a dear friend through the depths of grief; I rejoined the community at Bar Method Oakland and surprised myself with my strength; and I cooked many, many delicious meals. I’m proud of myself and deeply grateful for my community. Thank you for supporting my journey, for ordering all those new products and for reading this. 🥰💜

I’ve been feeling uninspired and down for the last month, going through my cycle of existential crisis and questioning of being an artist. Sometimes it’s hard to feel the joy of this profession when the job flow trickles and there’s too much time to think. I know I’ll feel better soon, the cycle will shift and I’ll feel fresh and light again - I can’t wait for that feeling. 🍂🍁

🎉 BIG NEWS!!! 🎉 

I’m opening my own brick & mortar shop!!! It’s called Sophie Tivona Paper and I will - of course - stock my entire line of paper products AND carry watercolor supplies and paints from @caseformaking!!! I will also offer small, in-person workshops in the space. 🥰
My tiny shop is located in Temescal Alley in Oakland, a thriving little community of shops and restaurants that feels like it was made for me. Follow along as I transform the space! @sophietivonapaper 💜 My grand opening will be April 16 and I’d love to see you there! 🥳
I’m not doing any crowd funding but if you’d like to support this new venture please buy some goodies from my shop! Or, if you’d really like to give without receiving (or want to buy me a celebratory cupcake) my Venmo is @Sophie-Tivona.💜 Thank you for your support, I feel so lucky to be starting this new adventure.

Now and Then! December 31, 2023 ⏮️ December 31, 2017!
Six years ago I never ever thought I’d open up my own shop. I was still working in a restaurant and doing illustration on the side, making menu designs and selling cards and prints online. I left the restaurant in October 2019 and have never looked back. The past few years of freelancing during the pandemic were unpredictable and lean… when I saw the tiny spot in Temescal Alley in February I felt in my gut that it was meant to be. And here I am, 10 months later - thriving and feeling confident and proud! This leap of faith was so scary but I felt my guides urging me to believe in myself. I’m so glad I did. Thank you for helping my little shop succeed, for each online purchase and Patreon membership and all the small things that have lifted my business up. I can’t wait to spend 2024 making more beautiful things! 🥰🥰🥰
